<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN277-intro">
      <p type="edition">tiṇai – tumpai; tuṟai – uvaikaik kaluḻcci. pūṅkaṇuttiraiyār.
      </p>
      <p xml:lang="en" type="translation">  
      </p>
    </div>
    <div xml:id="PN277">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>mīṉuṇ kokkiṉ ṟūvi yaṉṉa</l>
<l>vāṉaraik kūntaṉ mutiyōḷ ciṟuvaṉ</l>
<l>kaḷiṟeṟintu paṭṭaṉa ṉeṉṉu muvakai</l>
<l>yīṉṟa ñāṉṟiṉum peritē kaṇṇīr</l>
<l>nōṉkaḻai tuyalvarum vetirattu</l>
<l>vāṉpeyat tūṅkiya citariṉum palavē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>The joy, when they said “he has fallen attacking an elephant bull,</l>
<l>the son of the old woman with pure white tresses</l>
<l>like the feathers of a fish-eating egret,</l>
<l>it was greater than the day she gave birth [to him]. [Her] tears</l>
<l>are more than the drops that drip down, when it rains,</l>
<l>on the bamboo whose tough shafts come into swinging</l>
</lg>
    </div>
  </body>
